    <keyword>rmdir</keyword>
    <short_description>Supprime un répertoire.</short_description>
    <syntax>
        <syntax_item>rmdir(dirname)</syntax_item>
        <syntax_item>rmdir(dirname, 's')</syntax_item>
        <syntax_item>res = rmdir(dirname)</syntax_item>
        <syntax_item>res = rmdir(dirname, 's')</syntax_item>
        <syntax_item>[res, msg] = rmdir(dirname)</syntax_item>
        <syntax_item>[res, msg] = rmdir(dirname, 's')</syntax_item>
    </syntax>
    <param_input>
        <param_input_item>
        <param_name>dirname</param_name>
        <param_description
      >a string: nom du répertoire à supprimer.</param_description>
        </param_input_item>
        <param_input_item>
        <param_name>'s'</param_name>
        <param_description
      >a string: supprime aussi les sous-répertoires.</param_description>
        </param_input_item>
    </param_input>
    <param_output>
        <param_output_item>
            <param_name>res</param_name>
            <param_description>un booléen: true ou false.</param_description>
        </param_output_item>
        <param_output_item>
        <param_name>msg</param_name>
        <param_description>a string: message d'erreur ou ''.</param_description>
        </param_output_item>
    </param_output>
    <description>
      <p><b>res = rmdir(dirname)</b> supprime le répertoire <b>dirname</b>.</p>
      <p>Si le répertoire n'est pas vide, il faut utiliser l'argument 's'.</p>
        </description>
